gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Knicks 106, 76ers 79
gameRecap.excerpt: The Knicks defeated the 76ers, 106-79. Josh Hart recorded his fourth triple-double of the season as he put up 20 points, a career-high tying 19 rebounds and 10 assists for the Knicks, while Jalen Brunson added 20 points (4-8 3PT FG), four rebounds and nine assists in the victory. Tyrese Maxey tallied 17 points and four assists for the 76ers in the losing effort. The Knicks improve to 38-27 on the season, while the 76ers fall to 36-29.
